<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEF18E5AFD8FFD44" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEF18E5AFD8FFD44" blockId="29.[249,1230,512,1014]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Definition. Shell minute, rather high-spired, narrowly phaneromphalous. Surface ornament of spiral cords and opisthociine growth lines. Protoconch deviated; aperture simple, circular.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEF28E93FC14FC94" box="[298,910,743,783]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEF28E93FC14FC94" blockId="29.[249,1230,512,1014]" box="[298,910,743,783]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860F6B29FEF18F62FE4AFC02" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860F6B29FEF18F62FE4AFC02" blockId="29.[249,1230,512,1014]" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FE3C8F62FD43FCA6" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[484,729,790,829]" class="Gastropoda" genus="Palaeoalvania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FE3C8F62FD43FCA6" box="[484,729,790,829]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Palaeoalvania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860F6B29FBFA8F62FB07FCA6" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1058,1181,790,829]" class="Gastropoda" family="Elasmonematidae" genus="Kimina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860F6B29FBFA8F62FB07FCA6" box="[1058,1181,790,829]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="92">Kimina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shell and protoconch characters, but differs in having spiral cords.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
